rve fibres","Herring bodies","Fenestrated capillaries only"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior pituitary (adenohypophysis) contains a \u003Cstrong\u003Ereticulin supportive mesh\u003C/strong\u003E framework that supports the hormone-producing cells. \u003Cstrong\u003EPituicytes\u003C/strong\u003E are specialized glial cells found exclusively in the posterior pituitary. \u003Cstrong\u003EUnmyelinated nerve fibres\u003C/strong\u003E carrying vasopressin and oxytocin are found in the posterior pituitary. \u003Cstrong\u003EHerring bodies\u003C/strong\u003E are dilated nerve terminals containing neurosecretory granules found in the posterior pituitary. \u003Cstrong\u003EFenestrated capillaries\u003C/strong\u003E are found in both the anterior and posterior pituitary, not exclusively in one region.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior pituitary develops from Rathke\u0027s pouch (oral ectoderm) while the posterior pituitary develops from neural ectoderm, explaining their different cellular compositions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The anterior pituitary contains a reticulin framework that supports hormone-producing cells","Pituicytes are specialized glial cells found exclusively in the posterior pituitary","The anterior and posterior pituitary have distinct cellular compositions reflecting their different embryological origins"],"references":["Hormone supply to the pituitary gland: A comprehensive investigation of female\u2011related tumors (Review). Int J Mol Med. 2022 Oct;50(4):122. doi: 10.3892/ijmm.2022.5178. Epub 2022 Aug 10. PMID: 35946461; PMCID: PMC9387558","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrin